abstract: UNKNOWN WOMAN RUN OVER AND KILLED.-- On Saturday afternoon an unknown woman was run over in Greenwich-street, near Vesey, by a horse and cart,--the latter loaded with iron bars--and instantly killed. The driver, SAMUEL COURTNEY, was immediately arrested to await the result of the Coroner's inquest which was held yesterday. The evidence showed that the deceased ran suddenly in front of the cart, and was run over before the driver could stop the horse.

abstract: At ten minutes after 5 o'clock yesterday afternoon, the famous Crystal Palace, where the Fair of the American Institute was being held, took fire.
